From d08b09eb542cc1a1cc5128b5b6fb95f09f497c46 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: msn <msn@polaris.dev>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2026 11:37:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] I-ready-013 (#1080): clinical/benchmark report ships ONLY
 span-verified prose
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

The benchmark + any clinical run appended ~1500-3000 words of un-span-verified "Analyst Synthesis"
interpretive prose to report.md (the unverified layer ran because planner defaults off + the flag
defaults on + Gate-B set neither). §-1.1 risk + it undercuts the BEAT-BOTH faithfulness claim.

Fix (Codex brief-gate APPROVE, fix A_force_off): the clinical/benchmark path ships only the
span-verified multi-section prose; the unverified analyst layer is suppressed there. Faithfulness
machinery (strict_verify / 4-role D8 / provenance) UNTOUCHED; non-clinical off-mode byte-identical.
- generate_multi_section_report gains suppress_analyst_synthesis (default False = byte-identical) +
  an explicit PG_SWEEP_ANALYST_SYNTHESIS env-enabled check, both folded into the analyst-block gate.
- run_one_query forces it for any clinical-domain query (covers the pipeline-B UI: _infer_domain maps
  medical/health/pharma -> clinical).
- Gate-B slate sets PG_SWEEP_ANALYST_SYNTHESIS=0 via a new force-EXACT mechanism + a fail-closed
  preflight that ABORTS if the unverified layer is somehow on (no silent benchmark drift).

Provenance note: the initial implementation was produced by the codex-exec brief-review agent; I
(Claude) reviewed it line-by-line, verified faithfulness-safety + correct scoping, and authored the
behavioral/negative test coverage. A fresh independent Codex diff-gate reviews this committed diff.

24 verified-only tests (5 source-pin + 19 Claude-authored behavioral/negative: suppress wins,
env-kill, NON-clinical PRESERVED byte-identical, default-param, domain matrix, UI routing) + full
272-test dr_benchmark suite green.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
